The paper proposes a deep learning approach for bone segmentation from CT images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) domains. The application of the method is in the medical field, specifically for multiple myeloma, which suggests the medical imaging (cs.MED) category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of a UNet-inspired architecture, which is a popular deep learning model for image segmentation, indicating the deep learning (cs.DL) category.
